courses.learning_outcomes:
1. Define biomimicry, and explain how they lead to sustainable design solutions;
2. Identify and define a real world challenge;
3. Search and identify relevant nature’s strategies from credible sources;
4. Develop a sustainable design solution with a biomimetic approach;
5. Evaluate and share a conceptual design solution professionally to corresponding audiences;
6. Collaborate effectively with others
- -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. 定義仿生學，及解釋仿生學如何有助設計一個可持續的解決方案；
2. 釐清及界定一個現實世界的問題；
3. 從可靠的資料來源，找出與問題相關的大自然方案；
4. 使用仿生學方法，從概念上研發可持續的解決方案；
5. 評估解決方案及專業地向受眾分享；
6. 與團隊有效地合作

courses.feedback_evaluation:
1. Mutual expectations on the course administration, assessments and behaviors are established in the first lesson;
2. Students are welcome to share their feedback in any lesson;
3. Mid-course formative evaluation;
4. End of the course summative evaluation;
5. Feedback for improvement from the reflective activity after the last lesson of the course;
6. The staff-student consultative meeting held every year;
7. A forum in the course website.
